{
  "stem": "18056.1",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then before we knew, the Russians got together with the-- with the Germans and they came from the east into Poland.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So as I say, 10 days later, it was only Warsaw that they were fighting for.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Spring 1940, I was already in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That is-- you know, as the Germans saw that Lodz had a tremendous Jewish population, more than the 10% percentage, I don't know maybe 30% of-- of Jews lived-- 30% of the population in Lodz were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were in the textile business and it was a very industrious city.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so the Germans saw that this is not going to work, being all integrated and mixed, so they started to separate and build a ghetto around the area where the Jewish population was living in Lodz.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that's where the ghettos started.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So at that time, they were very tough, the Germans.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "They came into one building and there could have been maybe 80 or 100 people living in that building, apartments.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they would give 15 minutes or 20 minutes and say, you, get out, raus.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And we had to go someplace, so people were running to the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They said, here is where you're going to have to find a place to live.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And so this is-- this was how it started out right away.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 45,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was people who had something on them-- if they were smart, they either tried to move into the area where the ghetto was, or they would just run to Warsaw, run away, run east, because they thought that were the Russians are, it's going to be better.",
      "word_count": 48
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that's the way we came.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 46,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had to-- we had to go first to Lodz, because they said, if you stay in Konstantynow, you're going to get killed.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
